content: Currently working through the Python Fundamentals Track (20+ modular course). It's more expensive than Udemy, but it's obvious why. Production is very good. The USP for me was the interactive python shell. You're introduced to a concept via a video, then apply it using real data. You can learn at your own speed and complete a daily challenge on what module you're currently studying. Hugo is good at keeping you motivated, funny guy.
The application is incredible. I shown great progress on python, thanks very much.
The app is quite user friendly, makes python learning easy, I always look forward to my daily challenge
if you're looking to learn python you wouldn't be disappointed

DataCamp is helping me learn the fundamentals in Python, and with a good pace I believe I will one day graduate from a beginner to a pro. I love the simplicity of the lessons and tests, my progress is tracked... I will suggest DataCamp for everyone, both those who want to learn python on desktop (the desktop experience is amazing) and on mobile.
Great app to learn python,describe the subject in a easy and considerable way with challenging practice exercises.So good for beginners.
It's very challenging and best app for learning python

DataCamp makes learning data science easy. I've used this app to help me learn R and Python and because it's on my phone, I can learn while on the train, while waiting for an appointment or even sitting on my couch. I would love it if the app had quick reference guides that I can call up anytime or jump to a topic (like NumPy) so when I'm actually coding I can refer to DataCamp for help. I know cheat sheets are available on the web version. Also, how about a Pandas for python tutorial?

very awesome for practicing languge like python r and the challenges are good as par your level of learning pretty awesome to use this app easy to use ans best to learn this can be best to your daily practicing of your syntax and concepts practicing

Good job with the app but... I've finished the introduction to python two times in a row and the progress is lost after I'm connected to the internet. I just want to see the intermediate course. Please fix it and I'll change my rating! Keep up the nice work :-)

I love everything the team at datacamp are doing. Their subscription structure, the app, the learning by doing mentality, their emails. They're really going from strength to strength to help people learn r and python. The app itself is a work in progress, but I value they've released it early to get feedback from users. It's good but will only get better when more and more content becomes available
